<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-08-27.S1W-356.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80259" speakername="Andrew Wilson (Central Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S1W-356" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0827.htm#356">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what was the value of land transferred out of public ownership in the Edinburgh Royal Infirmary Private Finance Initiative agreement.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-08-27.S1W-356.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80146" speakername="Susan Deacon" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0827.htm#356">

  <p>The excess sites sold to Morrison Construction Limited as part of the Private Finance Initiative contract for the new Royal Infirmary of Edinburgh, namely the City, Princess Margaret Rose and Dental Hospitals were valued by the District Valuer at between &pound;10m and &pound;11.5m and by the Trust&#146;s property advisers, Ryden International, at &pound;10.85m. The valuations were detailed in the Full Business Case Addendum published earlier this year by the Trust.</p>

</reply>


